detailedRequirements:
Task Overview

NASA need to develop a software version of the Solution Mechanism Guide so that users can navigate a search form to a filtered subset of solution mechanisms that are a best fit for their specific needs based on the criteria they input (experience similar to finding a car rental or airline ticket online but more fun and NASA-y).

The scope of this challenge is to updat the provied UI prototype to support the print functionality in the outlined pages below.

Task Requirements

The following pages have print functionality and they must be implemented in the UI prototype (When user click on print button it will open up the print preview page) :

  • smg_listing.html
    • screenshot : 03_1_Identify-Solution_List_print-friendly.png
    • The screenshot only show preview of "List" print, you also need to support print of "Grid" view.
  • smg_details.html
    • screenshot : 04_Solution-Details_print-friendly.png
  • smg_compare.html
    • screenshot : 05_Compare_print-friendly.png
  • help_topics_listing.html
    • screenshot : 6_0_Help-Topics-print-friendly.png
    • notice buttons are not shown in the print preview
  • help_topics_details.html
    • screenshot : 6_1_Help-Topics-educational-details-print-friendly.png
  • examples_listing.html
    • screenshot : 7_1_2Examples_print-friendly.png
    • notice that buttons are not part of the print preview
  • example_details.html
    • screenshot : 07_2_2Examples_details_print-friendly.png

You also need to fix the following issues :

  • In add/edit smg page (smg_admin_add_edit_smg.html) in step 4 we have updated examples content section as shown in this screenshot below (we added tabs when you click on example name it changes content). You need to update examples section in smg_admin_details.html page, smg_listing.html smg details popup (when click on smg image) and smg_details.html page to match it.
  • In smg_admin_add_edit_smg.html page step 2, when adding new example, add "remove example" button in the current example. for example, when you open step 2, you will see one example, if you click 'add more example' it will add another one below it but you cannot delete the example at top, so add 'remove example' button with same style as 'add more example' to the examples above the one with 'add more example' one.

Documents provided

UI prototype and Storyboard is provided in challenge forums.

Deliverables

Updated UI Prototype.
